    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Open your settings.xml file <code>~/.m2/settings.xml</code>  (create it if it doesn't exist). Add a section with the properties added. Then make sure the <code>activeProfiles</code> includes the new profile.</p>\n<pre class=\"lang-xml prettyprint-override\"><code>&lt;settings&gt;\n\n   &lt;!-- ... other settings here ... --&gt;\n\n    &lt;profiles&gt;\n        &lt;profile&gt;\n            &lt;id&gt;downloadSources&lt;/id&gt;\n            &lt;properties&gt;\n                &lt;downloadSources&gt;true&lt;/downloadSources&gt;\n                &lt;downloadJavadocs&gt;true&lt;/downloadJavadocs&gt;\n            &lt;/properties&gt;\n        &lt;/profile&gt;\n    &lt;/profiles&gt;\n\n    &lt;activeProfiles&gt;\n        &lt;activeProfile&gt;downloadSources&lt;/activeProfile&gt;\n    &lt;/activeProfiles&gt;\n&lt;/settings&gt;\n</code></pre>\n<p>Edit: As mentioned by Jingguo Yao, this works with Eclipse IDE only - the same can also be configured in your IDE of choice. In Elcipse via Window -&gt; Preferences -&gt; Maven menu, though this probably has to done at every workspace level and for fresh Eclipse installations.</p>\n<p>Alternatively configure the <code>maven-dependency-plugin</code> in your <code>pom.xml</code> in a separate profile and run it as required - keeping it in the main build will lead to build times (needlessly elongating (not to mention space) at places like your build nodes that don't need either sources or java docs. Preferable this should configured in some org or division parent <code>pom.xml</code>, otherwise it has be repeated everywhere in different places</p>\n"
  }, {
