    "creation_date" : 1456510109,
    "answer_id" : 35658751,
    "question_id" : 5780758,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Answer for people from Google</p>\n<p>In <strong>Eclipse</strong> you can manually download <strong>javadoc</strong> and <strong>sources</strong>.</p>\n<p>To do that, right click on the project and use</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Maven -&gt; Download JavaDoc</li>\n<li>Maven -&gt; Download Sources</li>\n</ul>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 4070522,
      "reputation" : 5402,
      "user_id" : 3343801,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/f516c2bdc196689bb2a9e65be876b8d3?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "Venkateswara Rao",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/3343801/venkateswara-rao"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 58,
    "last_activity_date" : 1533557841,
    "last_edit_date" : 1533557841,
    "creation_date" : 1464269666,
    "answer_id" : 37462423,
    "question_id" : 5780758,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Just consolidating and prepared the single command to address source and docs download...</p>\n\n<pre><code>mvn dependency:sources dependency:resolve -Dclassifier=javadoc\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 388788,
      "reputation" : 1088,
      "user_id" : 747917,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 33,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/71129109baab1673748ad7e67724cf99?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Ahmad Muzakki",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/747917/ahmad-muzakki"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 10,
    "last_activity_date" : 1467430041,
    "creation_date" : 1467430041,
    "answer_id" : 38156205,
    "question_id" : 5780758,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>On <strong>NetBeans</strong> : \nopen your project explorer->Dependencies->[<em>file.jar</em>] rightclick->Download Javadoc</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 2997947,
      "reputation" : 7829,
      "user_id" : 2544089,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/8bbb02dede49f7102b95b296157eb4fb?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Mario Rossi",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/2544089/mario-rossi"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 1,
    "last_activity_date" : 1553497768,
    "creation_date" : 1553497768,
    "answer_id" : 55332737,
    "question_id" : 5780758,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Simply modify file <code>mvn</code> (or <code>mvn.cmd</code> if in windows) and add whatever command line switches you need (as mentioned by other answers).  If you don't want to modify the install files (which I'd recommend), create a <code>mymvn</code> (or <code>mymvn.cmd</code>) wrapper that invokes the regular <code>mvn</code> with the parameters.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 7444245,
      "reputation" : 1229,
      "user_id" : 5661010,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 33,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/5ysHx.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "iLearn",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5661010/ilearn"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1568129819,
    "creation_date" : 1568129819,
    "answer_id" : 57874098,
    "question_id" : 5780758,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>I had to use KeyStore to Download the Jars. If you have any Certificate related issues you can use this approach:</p>\n\n<pre><code>mvn clean install dependency:sources -Dmaven.test.skip=true -Djavax.net.ssl.trustStore=\"Path_To_Your_KeyStore\"\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>If you want to know how to create KeyStores, this is a very good link:\n<a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/25911623/problems-using-maven-and-ssl-behind-proxy\">Problems using Maven and SSL behind proxy</a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1535921,
      "reputation" : 3588,
      "user_id" : 1431979,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/07cf3a083f484ce5c01ef38a3a9ad917?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Pierre C",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1431979/pierre-c"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1569770086,
    "creation_date" : 1569770086,
    "answer_id" : 58156525,
    "question_id" : 5780758,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>In Netbeans, you can instruct Maven to check javadoc on every project open :</p>\n\n<p><code>Tools</code> | <code>Options</code> | <code>Java</code> icon | <code>Maven</code> tab | <code>Dependencies</code> category | <code>Check Javadoc</code> drop down set to <code>Every Project Open</code>.</p>\n\n<p>Close and reopen Netbeans and you will see Maven download javadocs in the status bar.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 1782478,
      "reputation" : 1526,
      "user_id" : 1624839,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/040196ed887e3633755f1c491fb8367b?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Mehdi",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1624839/mehdi"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 0,
    "last_activity_date" : 1572017933,
    "creation_date" : 1572017933,
    "answer_id" : 58561651,
    "question_id" : 5780758,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>For the sources on dependency level ( pom.xml) you can add :</p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;classifier&gt;sources&lt;/classifier&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 67765,
      "reputation" : 5159,
      "user_id" : 198108,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 79,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0d61e8dd1d552643c997a61442ac197b?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "javydreamercsw",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/198108/javydreamercsw"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 3,
    "last_activity_date" : 1704440071,
    "last_edit_date" : 1704440071,
    "creation_date" : 1584020084,
    "answer_id" : 60655257,
    "question_id" : 5780758,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>To follow up on the answer from <a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/users/257299/kevinarpe\">kevinarpe</a> this does both sources and Javadocs:</p>\n<pre><code>&lt;build&gt;\n  &lt;plugins&gt;\n    &lt;plugin&gt;\n      &lt;groupId&gt;org.apache.maven.plugins&lt;/groupId&gt;\n      &lt;artifactId&gt;maven-dependency-plugin&lt;/artifactId&gt;\n      &lt;version&gt;3.1.1&lt;/version&gt;\n      &lt;executions&gt;\n        &lt;execution&gt;\n          &lt;goals&gt;\n            &lt;goal&gt;sources&lt;/goal&gt;\n            &lt;goal&gt;resolve&lt;/goal&gt;\n          &lt;/goals&gt;\n        &lt;/execution&gt;\n      &lt;/executions&gt;\n      &lt;configuration&gt;\n        &lt;classifier&gt;javadoc&lt;/classifier&gt;\n      &lt;/configuration&gt;\n    &lt;/plugin&gt;\n  &lt;/plugins&gt;\n&lt;/build&gt;\n</code></pre>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 14673482,
      "reputation" : 659,
      "user_id" : 10597330,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/e8fd783c0f39f6ba92064b648eb5f496?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
      "display_name" : "GilbertS",
